text.tspan: Extremely significant among the Nigerian tribes is omugwo. After a mother gives birth to her baby, her
mother-in-law comes to the home to take care of the new mother and the baby. The nursing mother is not
required to lift a finger as everything is done by her mother-in-law. This tradition called "omugwo" means:
Extremamente significativo entre as tribos nigerianas omugwo. Depois que uma me d a luz a seu beb, sua sogra vem para casa cuidar
da nova mame e do beb. A me que amamenta no obrigada a levantar um dedo, pois tudo feito pela sogra. Esta tradio chamada
